14 (17) “Individual health benefit plan” means a health benefit plan:
15 (a) That is issued to an individual policyholder; or
16 (b) That provides individual coverage through a trust, association or similar group, regardless
17 of the situs of the policy or contract.
18 (18) “Initial enrollment period” means a period of at least 30 days following commencement of
19 the first eligibility period for an individual.
20 (19) “Late enrollee” means an individual who enrolls in a group health benefit plan subsequent
21 to the initial enrollment period during which the individual was eligible for coverage but declined
22 to enroll. However, an eligible individual shall not be considered a late enrollee if:
23 (a) The individual qualifies for a special enrollment period in accordance with 42 U.S.C. 300gg
24 or as prescribed by rule by the Department of Consumer and Business Services;
25 (b) The individual applies for coverage during an open enrollment period;
26 (c) A court issues an order that coverage be provided for a spouse or minor child under an
27 employee’s employer sponsored health benefit plan and request for enrollment is made within 30
28 days after issuance of the court order;
29 (d) The individual is employed by an employer that offers multiple health benefit plans and the
30 individual elects a different health benefit plan during an open enrollment period; or
31 (e) The individual’s coverage under Medicaid, Medicare, TRICARE, Indian Health Service or a
32 publicly sponsored or subsidized health plan, including, but not limited to, the medical assistance
33 program under ORS chapter 414, has been involuntarily terminated within 63 days after applying for
34 coverage in a group health benefit plan.
35 (20) “Multiple employer welfare arrangement” means a multiple employer welfare arrangement
36 as defined in section 3 of the federal Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, as amended,
37 29 U.S.C. 1002, that is subject to ORS 750.301 to 750.341.
38 (21) “Preexisting condition exclusion” means a limitation or exclusion of benefits or a denial of
39 coverage based on a medical condition being present before the effective date of coverage or before
40 the date coverage is denied, whether or not any medical advice, diagnosis, care or treatment was
41 recommended or received for the condition before the date of coverage or denial of coverage.
42 (22) “Premium” includes insurance premiums or other fees charged for a health benefit plan,
43 including the costs of benefits paid or reimbursements made to or on behalf of enrollees covered by
44 the plan.
45 (23) “Rating period” means the 12-month calendar period for which premium rates established
