8 of a short term health insurance policy issued by the insurer to the policyholder.
9 (26) “Small employer” means an employer who employed an average of at least one but not more
10 than 50 full-time equivalent employees on business days during the preceding calendar year and who
11 employs at least one full-time equivalent employee on the first day of the plan year, determined in
12 accordance with a methodology prescribed by the Department of Consumer and Business Services
